description: Our 11th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly – the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world’s finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Volume 11

description:
Charlie Hodged

The heroes of two generations gather to pay their respects to a fallen comrade. Meanwhile, Mettle and Metalman finally face the reality of coexisting on the same Earth. Plus--secrets revealed as we delve into the origins of the members of the Association!
name: Charlie Hodged

description: The Broadsword saga continues with stories that range from the ridiculous to the horrific. Broadsword Zombies! Dragons! And one Mean Nurse! It's all here. Art by guest artists James Johnson (Mutant Comix), Vince Andrews (Spacedogs), and Andreas Knoll (Quantanaut).

After coming under attack while attempting to extract, Grasshead and her squad find themselves stuck on the outskirts of Dubai. With night approaching, they need to rendezvous with their support team at the downtown safe house-- but the eyes of the enemy are everywhere and nothing is what it seems.

Rebekah Belle is in danger after manifesting superpowers and being labeled a witch. Now she and her 'coven' strike back against those who are hunting them. The action culminates in an epic showdown against a superstitious preacher that will blow you away. Read as major events in history are brought to life through the eyes of superheroes past.
name: Chapter III

description:
The Last Firewall

Pushed to the breaking point, Roger and Nova attempt to steal back Roger's research from the deepest laboratories hidden below the Earth Science Guild. But this also means crossing paths with a very serious man wearing a mask... A man with origins and motives that NEED to be heard.

This issue is extra-long, coming in at 30 pages of sequential art, with additional cover art and sketches.
name: The Last Firewall

description: Moon Girl #2 is an exact replica of this scarce 1947 comic including all ads and editorial content. The issue expands to 52 pages with stories by Shelly Moldoff and Johnny Craig. The artwork is fully restored and in keeping with the classic feel of the artwork. Full color.

The members of Jenny Jump seem poised to finally capitalize on their intellectual larceny and hit the big time, but things get even weirder when they encounter a woodland cult with plans of their own.
name: Volume 3

description:
Revelations

As the team reels from a tragic loss, Pyre is given a glimpse of what is to come from the mysterious Tempora, while a new villain attacks Versipellis at his school.
name: Revelations

description:
A Tiger in the Cage

The Odysseys are enjoying some sun in the great city of Ankara, Turkey, when out of the blue a group of high-tech mercenaries kidnap the kids. As Doctor Odyssey and John rush to save the children, they find themselves caught... much like A Tiger in the Cage. The group demands Doctor Odyssey to build a battery for their war machine - or else! It's a tight spot for our family. Can the Odysseys get out?
name: A Tiger in the Cage

description:
In "Love in a Bottle," two young lovers try to escape their past only to venture into a future that leaves everything in doubt.

An underwater heist in San Francisco has some unexpected results as a hidden treasure long-buried reveals its mysteries in "Wanton Destruction." Plus monsters and bombs.

The fourth issue of SHORTS + LOSSES goes full color for widescreen action, adventure and excitement.

After their altercation with the space pirates, Lasha and Rover stop for fuel, which ends up leading them on a small detour. One that leads to a few tense moments.

They also meet an interesting guy named Lance, who's a little too quick on the trigger-finger.

Escalations!

Who are Press and Madame Macro and why do they hate our sanguine speedster? You'll find all the answers here as Startup's incredible origin tale continues to unfold! If you have an appetite for action and a thirst for thrills, you must not miss this instant classic from writer Darin Henry (Seinfeld, Futurama, KC Undercover), artist Craig Rousseau (Batman Beyond, Harley Quinn), colorist Glenn Whitmore, letterer Marshall Dillon and featuring a cover by the legendary Sal Buscema (Spider-Man, Avengers)!
name: Escalations!

description:
Vox Populi, Part Two

With Blaine and his marauders holding the Unforgiven hostage, and government troops arriving any second--can the rebels make their broadcast to the world and escape with their lives?
name: Vox Populi, Part Two

description:
Iron Fist

Before they say goodbye to one of their own, our heroes must first contend with a rampaging robot and an insidious plot that finds two enemies fighting over the fate of a friend!
name: Iron Fist

description:
Hero

In chapter 1 the story begins. We meet Hakim, Luke, Sebastian (ordinary teenagers from London) and an Almier.
name: Hero

description: Russell McClain is a man out for revenge. His father was driven to his death by bad deals and an unscrupulous man, losing his farm in the process. Over a dozen years later, Russell’s revenge is nearly complete—his enemy’s happiness and finances are in ruin. When the man’s stepdaughter reappears to collect the last remnants of her once-extravagant lifestyle from their old house, her arrival might just give Russell one last thing to ruin. Can love stop Russell’s total domination of his enemies or will revenge conquer all?
name: Vol. 1

description: Dying after a life of suffering, Jenny’s mother’s last words to her were to never marry a poor man. Jenny, a maid in Scotland, grew up with this lessonWhen she hears that a man who found success in the New World is looking for a bride, she boards a ship crossing the Atlantic. However, when the ship encounters a storm and she falls into the sea, Harris, a rumored misogynist, dives into the ocean and rescues her.When she awakes, she is in the New World. And he, the man who glared at her with scorn when she saw him in town, saved her? While traveling together to meet her husband-to-be, Jenny feels herself drawn to Harris despite his reputation and despite her best intentions.
name: Vol. 1

description: A savage from the steppes like BRAM takes only what he needs, when he needs. And now he needs revenge. Chasing the traitor ABDUL ASAN, BRAM arrives to the ancient city of Dumares. BRAM, in his wanders, has seen many cities, including the most prosperous, the most just, the most cruel. But Dumares otdoes them all because, besides having all these sins and virtues, it has a secret... the secret of the air: the magic carpets. The dream of flight is only possible in Dumares. Bram will try to steal the secret. A secret that will put him on the trail of his enemy, who has unleashed unspeakable horrors, having desecrated the last remaining garden of Eden, where the force of creation remains immaculate.
name: The Last Eden

description: Franny’s always enjoyed competing with her brothers, and this is their new bet: Can she find a good match in just one month? The only problem is she knows nobody who is suitable. All of a sudden, her brothers’ best friend, Brett, comes to visit. He was her first love, and he’s still a handsome man. To her confusion, he invites her on a date—little does she know he’s trying to help her win the bet…
name: Vol. 1

description: Desperate for a large sum of money to save her ailing grandmother, Flavia goes to beg from her father, the man who abandoned her when she was a toddler. His price? Flavia must play the part of the ideal socialite and help her father curry the favor of an important client. Leon Maranz, the client in question, is handsome to the point of perfection, but Flavia knows that any associate of her father’s must be ruthlessly materialistic. And yet, the moment she catches a glimpse of Leon, sweet shivers run up Flavia’s spine…
name: Vol. 1

description: The Earl’s Secret—Jennifer has fallen deeply in love with an earl she met while at his castle in Scotland. The two of them have gotten close to one another very quickly, sharing a heated romance. However, even after they are bound together, the earl'’s cold words deeply injure her. The Pirate’s Kiss—Lucinda has left behind the memories of her youthful past and become a sensible governess to a young woman. But one night, she sees something unbelievable in the garden—her former fiancé, Daniel de Lancey, who abandoned her to become a pirate.
name: Vol. 1

description:
High Costs

Throughout time, Golems have been activated to protect god's chosen people from Inquisitions, Pogroms and even the Holocaust. But in modern Florida, Sandy the Golem must face a pharmaceutically engineered heavy to help Earth's most mystic retirement village. Did we mention the time travelling steam punk pirate?
name: High Costs

description: Gianna’s marriage is haunted by suspicion. Her husband, Franco, the man she’s loved since she was a girl, is the young CEO of an international corporation. However, their marriage is political, not one built on love. Unaware of Franco’s true feelings, Gianna’s confidence is smashed to pieces when his ex-girlfriend, the world-renowned actress Famke, appears. Despite being married to a millionaire herself, Famke has returned to seduce Franco and scorns Gianna as being nothing more than Franco’s PR wife, kept only for the sake of appearances. And, to make matters worse, Famke’s outrageous conduct has the gossip magazines raving!
name: Vol. 1

description: After her mother’s passing, Joanna lives a life wandering visiting casinos with her gambler father. Joanna’s kindness will not allow her to abandon her father, who has her dress as a prostitute at the casinos to distract his opponents and turn the game in his favor. One day, her father participates in a private game hosted by the Greek millionaire Vassos, but a crushing defeat burdens him with an enormous debt… Then, the millionaire cruelly tells him with a smile: “I willoffers him one escape—he’ll forget forgive the debt if you her father gives Joanna to me himthe woman.”
name: Vol. 1

description: It ain't easy being super, man. The Ideal is the world's greatest hero, but nobody knows where he came from, what he wants, or what his plans are... until now. Featuring the origin of The Ideal and his many adventures, The Ideal is the hero we need, whether we want or deserve him (or not).

For Katya the worst realization wasn’t the baby, it was knowing she’d fallen in love with Benedetto… Italian count and star surgeon Benedetto Medici is a notorious playboy. For Katya Petrova, a nurse with working-class roots, the gorgeous Italian was an object to venerate and admire from afar…until one night she saw Benedetto’s despair at losing the one he loved. How could she have known he was looking only for fleeting comfort in her arms?
name: Vol. 1

description: Even though her husband is a count, Miranda never really thought about their social status. But then, one day, after nothing but happy times between them, Dante suddenly calls Miranda a harlot and disappears with their son. Miranda, not understanding the reason behind this, is obviously bewildered, but then Dante contacts her again out of the blue. He tells her to come at once to his villa in Italy. Miranda goes to the villa, hoping to question her husband about how he’s treated her, but when she sees how wealthy he truly is, it only makes her realize how powerless she is…
name: Vol. 1

description:
THE BIG BANG

The year is 1999 and there is a battle going on in the city of Chicago. Frank has in his possession, a classic watch to control his life-time. His motives are not known, nor do we know the motives of the other side, the drifters.

In this first issue of Life-Time, Writer/artist Pramit Santra tries to introduce you to the main player of this story and start it with a Bang. From the streets of Chicago to the grand harbors of 1800s France, Life-Time is a tale of a misfortune. This is a story unbiased of whatever humanity feels or wants. This is not about bringing down the walls, this is about bringing down the whole creation.
name: The Big Bang

description:
Elya Virk arrives in a new city and immediately finds herself in trouble. Her first interaction with a prostitute and a pimp ends with horrific violence.

However, her efforts to find a job and a place to live seem to be paying off, even if it's by very strange means.

Kill It Before It Grow

Effortlessly magnificent, foremost and fair, MORDAWWA might just be the most reasonable ruler Hell has ever had - which is probably why everything is about to go horribly wrong. Whether this is a brand-new story, or the epic conclusion of a 666-issue saga, the question remains the same - who shot the Sheriff?
name: Kill It Before It Grow

description: During World War II, an injured U.S. Army paratrooper is rescued and nursed back to health by a beautiful, mysterious French woman. They fall in love and spend the next several decades together, but when a German soldier appears at their door one day, will the veil of their idyllic life be shattered?

A New Ride-- One Shot

In Perfect Storm: A New Ride, former FBI special agent Erin Storm is back--and none too pleased with her new assignment.
name: A New Ride

description: Redd Velvette was the captain of her own Pirate ship. Now Redd, and her faithful companion, Lass are stranded on a deserted island. This first issue of a new series explains how they ended up there. Included is the original 24 page comic, plus an 8 page backup story featuring Lass, in this fun and sexy tale.

Caitlyn’s nickname in school was Bookworm. She never did anything girly. Instead, all she did was study. She was too tall and had a flat chest and was far from being considered a cute girl. That’s why she always thought that love wasn’t for her. That is, until Rafaelo, a handsome Spanishmarquis,appears in front of her!
name: Vol. 1

description: Strength is a young superhero. When she loses her clothes in a televised supervillian battle, she finds herself condemned by the media and the government, even though her actions saved the city.

Strength is on the run, defeating supervillians without any clothing. Her defiance has ignited followers of all kinds, while she finds caught up in a political firestorm across the land. Branded an enemy of the state, the government orders American Patriot to defeat her. However, the fact that a woman has defeated an enemy he never could has only made him more mentally unstable.

This 32 Page Final Issue concludes Strength's tale!

Next Testament

History repeats itself as man once again finds himself at war with what is considered different. A difference marked by supernatural powers manifested through faith. Who are these new humans? Are they even human? Should they be feared? Are they people of God or soldiers of Hell? Faith will be tested in the new Spiritual Renaissance and only The Stronger will survive.
name: Next Testament

description: Una the Blade: an ongoing comic series about a barbarian single-mom on a dying Earth. Written and drawn by Steve LeCouilliard with guest stories drawn by an all-star roster of award-winning and up and coming cartoonists!
name: Vol. 1

description:
It is the first day of School at the Alexander Academy for Talented Young Individuals. Time to meet the Undergrad Heroes, six of the most unlikely Super Powered individuals you have ever met.

There is the shy and timid Cassandra (Cassy) Albright. The enormously dimwitted Alec Kholec, as well as the chain smoking Dustin Haze. Along with the super cool Terry Duece, and his hot (and hot tempered) twin sister Sherry. Finally the impossibly unlucky Kevin Lu-Zer, completes our ensemble.

Being the first day of college it's time for that awkward get to know your roommate stage. Six young adults, put together with no prior knowledge of each other, and they all have newly discovered Super Powers. What could possibly go wrong.

first_appearance_locations.name: Alexander Academy For Talented Young Individuals

location_credits.name: Alexander Academy For Talented Young Individuals

description: Wander enters the Aerial Labyrinth in an attempt to reunite with his lost love, Daisy. Along the way he meets a companion and does battle with a massive Guardian!
Step into Warp Zone ... Your life will never be the same.

Collecting the first 4 chapters of the webcomic... that's 200 comics! Witness the awkward first meeting between Anna and her unlikely succubus friend Izzy, and ridiculously sexy series of events that happen afterward.

This also includes the first three Slipshine bonus comics and bonus story that got inserted as a Kickstarter stretch reward. It's a big ol' 12"x12" book, 132 pages+cover, full color.
name: Vol. 1
Princess Elaine's Terrible Fate; Dangerous Plight of Princess Elaine
Priscilla, Queen of Escapes; Poor Pamela
Ruth's Wild West Adventures; Lina Foils Female Western Bandits; Captives in Distress
Baroness Steel; Adventures of Baroness Steel

description:
My Name is Hurl!

Spectromancer is back at it, and this time he is taking the fight to a Peeping Tom ghost! Spectro also sticks it to the 2016 presidential race, while dealing with the intricacies of furries. Meanwhile, we introduce the newest big bad of #IFightGhosts, Cthulhu himself!

Also inside: A special preview of the upcoming series "FETCH: An Odyssey"!
name: My Name is Hurl!

description:
The Gauntlet

Thanatos and Dinah are trapped in downtown Savannah and completely surrounded by zombies! Thanatos must use his guns and his guts to protect his small companion Dinah and himself from the undead!
name: The Gauntlet

description: All too often, the truth is a hard thing to accept ... especially when it emerges from the cursed mouth of a witch.

It's Zelda's welcome back party! Prepare yourself for a night of flirting, dancing, chowing-down, drinking, processing, and DRAMA! (Not to mention the morning-after hangovers... and the guests who decided to stay over!)

volume.name: The Collected Gay Black Boy Fantasy

description: Bruce's dad has fully arrived and is playing the long game.
In the aftermath of the tornado, Crystal battles Rachel face to face for control of a Spirit Jewel.

Battle 9

As Raid and June adjust to their new ally Tempest, Dae does his best to help Haze's depression and figure out the secret to these new bands.
name: Battle 9

description: From The Ashes is a dark fantasy tale about a realm on the brink of extinction. The survivors of a magical armageddon attempt to piece their world together and find a way to turn back the tide of evil. Desperate times make for unlikely alliances as a group of heroes fight a losing battle against a Necromancer of unimaginable power.

The three young gods stand their ground against the mightiest of hunters,Titan. Will this four-armed centaur stop the godling's freedom before it starts? Meanwhile the godling's blatant disregard for the laws of their kingdom begin to cause ripples of change across the universe.

Albert the Mail Squirrel

Workaholic flying squirrel Albert has his life turned upside down when his already hectic work schedule gets out of control. Can one tiny flying squirrel keep delivering mail to the whole of Goldwood Kingdom while taking care of his little sister? Get this cute slice-of-life comic today!
name: Albert the Mail Squirrel

description:
Father[s]

When Katherine 'Kat' Harlow was ten-years-old, she killed her parents. Showing no sign of remorse, she was said to be a girl devoid of conscience or soul - a Hollow Girl. Six years later, she reappeared as a brutal masked vigilante, avenging the dead with retributive violence.

That is what most people know about Hollow Girl. That's enough, right? Wrong.

Because there is a question that was never asked back when it all began, the answer to which changes everything.

Why?
name: Father[s] Part One of Two

description:
Found Out

The gang goes through Mike's shady dealings and realise they may have to prepare for the worst.
name: Found Out

description:
The "one-man anthology" officially becomes a misnomer with this issue since it includes a collaboration with filmmaker Troy Minkowsky entitled "Thomas O'Malley". It plays with the structure of a traditional British folk tale.

"Fade Away And Radiate" centers on a 1930's pulp hero whose novels have been completely forgotten and therefore must have his essence recycled into the collective consciousness. He's less than happy about this.

"Taking A Chance On Love" is, as the title implies, a story about forbidden love.

These stories are supplemented by an assortment of gag strips. There's also comics adaptations of poems by William Shakespeare and William Wordsworth.

Dephasing

A sinister plan is underway to separate Ariel from Xigi. Could Xigi survive the battle with the Four Horsemen?
name: Dephasing

description:
Mirror, Mirror Part 2

Kelly's purchase of a vampire mirror gets Vera into big trouble. Meanwhile, Jess's parents fear the worst after Jess confesses that Stewart is her boyfriend!
name: Mirror, Mirror (Part 2 of 3)

description: The death of King Edward has left an empty throne and mobilized the armies of three men who all believe that they are the rightful successor to rule England. Based on the Bayeux Tapestry, Bayeux tells the story of the events in and surrounding 1066 and the Norman and viking invasions of England.

Binary Noise Volume 1 is a science fiction story told through three vignettes - In a time when humans thrive throughout the Solar System, a homeless man and a space pilot are connected by unexpected events that deeply transform their lives. A world where technology is treated as mere vehicle for humans and as a shell for a newly-formed immature entity.

Story 1 - Infused Man:

In a futuristic world, a homeless man slowly dies in a dark city corner, until the appearance of a mysterious female cyborg and her assistant. What are their intentions? Why are they here looking for a man with absolutely nothing to offer?

Story 2 - Distant Argos:

A daughter in distress, and a cargo-ship heading to the far side of the Kuiper belt. A small crew dives into deep space looking for a rare metal in hope of fortune. An impossible job that may force tough decisions.

Story 3 - Electric Body:

A prison officer robot working on Jupiter's moon Europa becomes self-aware, a conscious entity that now pursues its own interests, an easy target to be manipulated by an unscrupulous prisoner.
name: Volume One

description: A special boy is born to an advanced alien race, called pranans, and is abducted by a demon lord. Divine Mother enlists a war goddess to go and rescue him.
A true tale of the cartoonist forced to work as the Easter Bunny in a mall after getting dotcom downsized in the early 2000's.

volume.name: Bunny Man: My Life in the Easter Charade

description:
The Provocation

The mechanical rebellion has begun. Caught off guard, the United States government attempts to save it's greatest asset, the President. But is it too late?
name: The Provocation

description: 40 color pages, comic anthology, 3 stories, 3 heroes, Xiuhcoatl, Arango and Verne

2116 AD: A menace from beyond the stars threatens the entire solar system and only the new genetically enhanced team of science heroes, the Solar Defenders, can save it. That is -- if they can conquer their self-doubt and stop jealously fighting amongst themselves. As they chase their powerful and implacable foe from distant Pluto to all the way back to Earth itself, it becomes clear that they can no longer be sure that the people around them are still human - not even themselves!
name: The Endless Incident

description:
Eternal Man Volume 1

A man who doesn't want to die gets his wish. Now what will he do?

Twilight of the Gods

Every century the Gods of Kennar must sleep for 30 years, in order to maintain their immortality. During this period, called Oloona Karsha, their souls enter in some humans, who will receive their powers and their personalities. But someone is plotting to kill the King of the Gods...
name: Twilight of the Gods

description: An exclusive ComiXology original short story introducing Eric Powell's new series Hillbilly!

A young girl survives a brutal massacre at a cabin party. Cops are clueless as to who or what could have done this, and the survivor's story is impossible to believe. The only two that can get to the bottom of this are not from this world!

Three tales of genius inventors, Saturday morning cartoon heroes and self-absorbed geeks! They will take you on adventures from the streets of Victorian

London to super-secret laboratories, and all the way into the vast reaches of space! A variety of comic book characters that will transport you to the wildest reaches of your imagination, as they right the wrongs, defend the confused and seek justice in the most unlikely of places. So get ready! It’s time for the Reckless Chronicles!

Time Traveling Team-Ups

The world of H.G. Wells' "Time Machine" has been reborn! Harland Wells is a lost soul who has spent most of his adult life searching for his father, who disappeared years before our story begins. Harland’s life takes a mysterious turn when he receives a letter confirming that his father is indeed alive, sending him on a journey into the unknown!

Hero Envy

The next great non-event begins here, in the first chapter of "Un-Original Sins"! On a secret moon base, deep in outer space, U-Toob the Pointer is binge watching the current season of "Game of Porcelain Thrones". Suddenly, his home is invaded by a mad man intent on stealing his powerful pointer! Once again, U-Toob must enlist the help of the "Hero Envy" gang, which has been reduced to a duo after their last adventure left them homeless, penniless, and minus two friends. The laughs have returned in this sequel to the acclaimed mini-series from RSP Productions!

Mighty Mascots

Six Cereal Mascots and one Soft Drink Pitchman are brought to electrifying life when an experimental formula explodes in a laboratory break room. Suddenly lost and confused, these powerful fledgling forces of justice must escape the evil clutches of Doctor Baneful, who is intent on exploiting and dissecting them! Their only ally is Manny Coleman, a washed up, former childhood actor turned scientist.

Based on the short story "Rikki-Tikki-Tavi"

from Rudyard Kipling's The Jungle Book.

A young mongoose raised to fear mankind is separated from his burrow during a fierce storm. He awakens in a human home with no memory of who or what he is. Now, with a pair of deadly king cobras targeting his new family and his memories slowly returning, he must choose between the values of the mongoose society he was born into and the humans he has come to care for.

Transmission

Robbie and Jehn have lived aboard Locksley Penitentiary all their lives, and in a few short weeks, they'll become full guards on the station. That's the plan, anyway, until a mysterious prisoner stirs up trouble and a royal spy arrives to investigate.
name: Transmission
